		<description><![CDATA[Scott, 

Well what can I say, about 6 months ago I started getting twitches and spasms in my left hand, mostly when I was playing or oddly doing D.I.Y. it really started to bother me especially as the Doctors and specialists started throwing around &quot;Parkinson&#039;s&quot; into the conversations. I stopped playing for a while which really upset me. I have been playing since I was 8 so some 33 years. I started back with my old band despite the twitching and have just learned to live wit it, some songs are more difficult than others, but I enjoy playing so much I don&#039;t let it bother me now, I tend to stick to simple runs but hey. Then I chanced upon your YOUTUBE and subsequently your website and what a revelation. I don&#039;t know if what you describe is the same as what I have but the other day I tried playing with latex gloves and whether it was psychosomatic or what, but it really made a difference. I cannot convey just how much reading about your condition and how you combat it has firstly made my bass playing more relaxed and trouble free, but it has changed my outlook on what my condition might  be. No more doom and gloom. So a huge huge thanks. Can I just ask though what gloves you use and where can I source them, I am eager to see if they make a bigger difference as the latex ones do, as you say they stick to the strings and don&#039;t really last.

Thanks again for the help. You are a life saver truly.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Scott, </p>
<p>Well what can I say, about 6 months ago I started getting twitches and spasms in my left hand, mostly when I was playing or oddly doing D.I.Y. it really started to bother me especially as the Doctors and specialists started throwing around &#8220;Parkinson&#8217;s&#8221; into the conversations. I stopped playing for a while which really upset me. I have been playing since I was 8 so some 33 years. I started back with my old band despite the twitching and have just learned to live wit it, some songs are more difficult than others, but I enjoy playing so much I don&#8217;t let it bother me now, I tend to stick to simple runs but hey. Then I chanced upon your YOUTUBE and subsequently your website and what a revelation. I don&#8217;t know if what you describe is the same as what I have but the other day I tried playing with latex gloves and whether it was psychosomatic or what, but it really made a difference. I cannot convey just how much reading about your condition and how you combat it has firstly made my bass playing more relaxed and trouble free, but it has changed my outlook on what my condition might  be. No more doom and gloom. So a huge huge thanks. Can I just ask though what gloves you use and where can I source them, I am eager to see if they make a bigger difference as the latex ones do, as you say they stick to the strings and don&#8217;t really last.</p>
<p>Thanks again for the help. You are a life saver truly.</p>
